      "blocks": {
        "cf-sidebar": {
          "type": "info",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Most first calls are short",
            "text": "<p>Thirty minutes is usually plenty. We'll ask questions, you'll ask questions, and we'll both know by the end whether it makes sense to keep talking.</p>"
          }
        },
        "cf-1": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What happens on the discovery call?",
            "answer": "<p>We talk. About your business, what you're doing now for accounting, what's working, what isn't. No slides, no sales deck. By the end we'll know whether we can help — and if we can, roughly what an engagement looks like.</p>"
          }
        },
        "cf-2": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What should I bring?",
            "answer": "<p>Nothing. If you have last year's return handy it can speed things up, but it's not required. The discovery call is about the conversation, not the paperwork.</p>"
          }
        },
        "cf-3": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How soon can we start?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients sign an engagement letter within a week of the call. For monthly engagements, full onboarding takes two to three weeks. For tax-only work during the off-season, we can often turn around a return in under a week.</p>"
          }
        },
        "cf-4": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you work with clients outside Texas?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Most of our clients are in Texas, but we work with small businesses and self-employed professionals across 22 states. All client communication happens by video, phone, and email — visits to the office are optional, not required.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "blocksOrder": ["cf-sidebar", "cf-1", "cf-2", "cf-3", "cf-4"]
